Text.Value: Yes I do.
That 'something' was the inimitable Crown of Karsus. You and Gortash absconded with it - catching the interest of a devil named Raphael.
That 'something' was the inimitable Crown of Karsus. Gortash absconded with it - catching the interest of a devil named Raphael.
Ever met an Orthon? I have - he told me you're a diabolist.
And yet you paid anyway. What a terrible cosmic coincidence.
Are you perchance a diabolist?
Then to piecemeal information we return. You wish for more knowledge, make me an offer.
Not a subtle point, but well made. Keep the Gauntlets. Your threats aren't necessary, but your coin is still welcome, devil-slayer.
You asked me to jog your memory. Jog I did. Our micro-pact is complete. Would you like to make another transaction?
You asked what I did for Lord Gortash, you paid the fee, and I answered you. Our pact is complete. Would you like to make another transaction?
Mammon! I knew it. I did!

EditorData.NodeContext: She already mentioned she had a bad feeling about this lady. Turns out she was right - she serves a devil called Mammon. Karlach isn't pleased about this but is glad she was right. Slightly comic, like she's expecting someone to challenge the fact that she knew it was Mammon (like saying 'I knew it!' after hearing an answer on jeopardy).

Text.Value: Raphael told me the Crown of Karsus was stolen from Mephistopheles - were you involved with that?
Did you help Lord Gortash retrieve some hellish curios by any chance?
Leave.
I want more information about your business with Gortash.
Where in the hells did the portal go?
Everything I took from the House is mine.
Likewise. Well, less of a colleague, more of a contractor - but I digress.
Finally, you were never here. That is of utmost import to remember. Now - begone.
I have, however, recently found a delightful new place I could sneak you into. Tell me, what do you know of the devil Raphael?
This should cover it. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
You are just no fun.
Raphael must have all kinds of secrets in his House, and I want to undress them.
This should cover it. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Show me your wares. The good stuff.
I welcome thee to the Devil's Fee, where every hellish curio is a - Oh. It's you.
If I managed it before, I can pull it off again.
I thought you'd never ask.
Not anymore.
Truly. That's remarkable. I like to deal with remarkable people. Very well.
Your wares! Bring them before me!
I'm impressed. And just a little bit intimidated.
I can't afford the fee.
Why not? Let's say I do.
*Raphael's warlock, Korrilla, mentioned a diabolist who aided Gortash. This cheerful woman doesn't seem the likeliest candidate.*
That information wasn't worth what I paid.
I've heard of it - seems like everyone is after this crown.
Far be it from me to overlook reason, reflected in the edge of a blade.
It's a front, really. I sell tacky, devil-shaped knick-knacks to plebians, and a more... refined set of wares to discerning customers. Like yourself.
I could remind you that you sought me, not vice versa. But you remember that surely. Have a good day.
I could remind you that you sought me, not vice versa. But why would I. I shall leave you in your blissful ignorance.
A generous donation... The King of Avarice's pockets are most pleased.
Hand them over, and our deal is done.
Bring him the Crown of Karsus, or he shall sup on my soul. Etc. Etc.
I have the money. Show me how to get to the House of Hope. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
OUT! The shop is closed. You and everyone else can go to hell - WITHOUT my help.
Ah how cute. You tried that last time too.
My word... This is embarrassing. Perhaps I should have explained our terms better.
I can see why your acquaintance with Raphael ended so violently - you're not a very convincing liar.
Your little scrote of a friend left this on my floor the last time you visited.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Helsik gives you Scleritas' hat. The DU takes it, non-plussed

Text.Value: In all the excitement, I hope you didn't forget our bargain. Do you have the Gauntlets?
My, what a juicy morsel. I didn't think he liked your type. Anyway...
But I'm afraid you'll need to offer an awful lot more than that. I'll be keeping the coin, though, of course.
I've decided to keep them.
Now you've seen what I have for thee - remember, discretion is key at the Devil's Fee.
Show me your goods.
Sure. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_3_01f129ea-b4dc-44b6-8154-9a948f876a82])
I'm intimately familiar with the lining of his pockets.
Very well. Here is the... What? I couldn't have misplaced... I've been robbed.
Time for a social call, then. I'm sure Raphael makes for a wonderful host.
Did I threaten you? Did I force the coin from your purse to mine? No. Pay up. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_3_01f129ea-b4dc-44b6-8154-9a948f876a82])
Then you'll hear no more of my tale.
I don't have that much money.
You're telling me wealth is an illusion? What part of 'Mammon worshipper' do you not understand?
Not interested.
You put me in a difficult position, mortal.
No, you're not getting more of my money.
Sounds like a deal. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_3_01f129ea-b4dc-44b6-8154-9a948f876a82])
I'm leaving. With the Gauntlets.
We have unfinished business - let's continue where we left off.
But, if you speak truth, perhaps I could... Jog that lazy memory of yours?
He's rather ambitious. One can only wonder what he has planned for the Crown. The answers to that can probably be found within his house...
Half it is. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
Your hoard of genuine infernal items is impressive - show me the really good stuff.
You seek answers, Lord Mammon seeks coin. I will happily mediate - make me an offer.
Sounds like a deal. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_7_4f22f91f-28ec-8f22-c546-1f8b69a2725a])
You... forgot what we did? I find that hard to believe.
We should infiltrate the devil's home. I have always dreamed of visiting the hells.
I'm also of the pact-bound persuasion - don't suppose I can have a free sample?
Leave.
I happened upon some of his correspondence that mentioned you dealings with him.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: We can learn this by reading the reports from Ninefingers or her necromancy book.

Text.Value: There are Gauntlets of Hill Giant Strength within the House of Hope. Free passage, and you fetch them for me. Deal?
Cut the price or I cut you into little pieces. CHOOSE.
Can you help me break into the House of Hope?
I knew you were a thief. Didn't realise you were a killer.
Let's keep this simple. I'd just like to trade.
I bested him in battle.
I already paid you too much. You are ripping me off.
You remember the Crown of Karsus, yes?
Toss a single coin to the diabolist.
Can you break me into the House of Hope?
I've never met you in my life.
I opened a portal for you and Lord Gortash.
I can reveal to you that I opened a portal for Lord Gortash.
Very well. How else may I be of service?
Shit, this again. Remind me of our past association?
Overdressed and overblown.
You want answers, you pay. Just like everyone else. Mammon is nothing if not egalitarian.
My offer still stands. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Pay [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6_ebf7de6b-4598-4feb-9c50-8083fc0fc59d] gold.
Perhaps a more banal transaction. May I see your wares?
I'm not paying that.
Ra-pha-el? That sounds vaguely familiar, but I have a terrible memory for names. The only thing that jogs it is coin.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sounding out the syllables of Raphael individually as if trying to remember if she's heard the name before, in an exaggerated performative manner

Text.Value: Here's [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_5_8860ed48-ba5f-4b7b-82bf-f1220f967d41] gold.
That can be arranged. If there's enough coin on the table, Mammon permits almost anything.
Never mind. Just show me your wares.
I have the money. Show me how to get to the House of Hope. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54]g)
Coin will do your corpse no good. SPEAK.
Such a task would be tantamount to suicide. And for what? The devil has nothing that you need.
Very well. If you wish to die in Avernus, that's your business. Mine is charging you for it.
I'm something of a diabolist myself - perhaps you could spare a little free knowledge?
That's a steep sum - I need some time to mull this over.
Mull, or don't mull. It matters not to me. If you have coin, return. If not - don't.
Let's see what you've got on offer.
Not as much as I'd like.
I serve a creature not unlike Lord Mammon - surely you can lower the price.
Look, we both know your patron doesn't need that much. Lower the price.
Then get out of my sight - and don't come back until your pockets drag with gold.

EditorData.NodeContext: deeply insulted by the player's cheek

Text.Value: There's nothing Mammon likes less than a welcher. Get the hell out and never come back.
There's no fun in that - so I think not. Make an offer, mortal.
Deal. Let's do this.
I can't afford the fee.
Oh no - definitely something up with this one. Trust me.

EditorData.NodeContext: Karlach has a bad feeling about a very chipper shopkeeper (and she's right).

Text.Value: Leave.
I want to know about Gortash's dealings in the hells.
With regards to the House of Hope...
Pay [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_5_8860ed48-ba5f-4b7b-82bf-f1220f967d41] gold.
Break into the House? If we were found, I doubt we'd come back.
Come now. Don't be miserly.
My most perceptive prospective customer... Welcome back.
Toss a coin to the diabolist.
You also attracted the attention of another devil: Raphael.
Let's poke around the rat's nest. Maybe set it on fire on the way out.
Coin and time most fortuitously spent.
We were lovers. It was all very steamy.
I do enjoy a good tangent. I have found a way to slip the latch to his house, if you wish to leap into Avernus one more time. The crown seemed to interest you after all.
We had a deal.
The first hit's free, eh? My, you have changed. Fine. Just this once.
The first hit's free, eh? Fine - I'll humour you, mortal. Just this once.
Looks like we owe Raphael a semi-friendly visit.
I am afraid that I cannot take you back to Mephistopheles' vaults. That place is now locked tighter than Lord Mammon's coinpurse.
How about [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6_ebf7de6b-4598-4feb-9c50-8083fc0fc59d] gold?
And then I... Gosh, my fickle memory fails. If only something would jog it.
Trips to the hells are usually one-way. Especially when the traveller causes the kind of trouble you did.
I welcome thee to the Devil's Fee, where every hellish curio's a rarity! So merry be - and shop with glee.
Begone. The Devil's Fee is closed for business.
Is this a joke? You can't give me what you don't have.
You must be awfully familiar with our esteemed Archduke to know about a thing like that.
My my... touchy subject I see. Very well.
I'm a skilled thief - give me free passage I'll bring you back a 'souvenir'.
No. Sounds too dangerous.
Looks like we owe Raphael a housecall.
Well, adjusting for inflation... appreciable value of knowledge but factoring in a dead-as-doornails Archduke... There we are. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_7_4f22f91f-28ec-8f22-c546-1f8b69a2725a])
Pay [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_4_5dac5eea-faeb-459c-b675-46c51519b784] gold.
Ah. Him again. Why is it always him?
Leave.
A most excellent decision.
Adjusting for inflation, the appreciable value of knowledge, Lord Mammon's tithe... A-ha. There we are. ([LOW_DevilsFee_GortashInfoPayment_4feace82-e2ce-a19d-967c-2a346b2cf96d])
For a fellow diabolist? I can stoop lower. Once.
Such a task would be tantamount to suicide. Do not even entertain it.
I've seen this scam before, it's cheaper to pay up front. How much to tell me everything?
How much to tell me everything about your dealings with Gortash?
You are almost certain to fail. Almost. And so, there is a chance you might succeed.
Actually I'll just take a look at your usual wares, if you don't mind.
I'm asking the questions here.
Definitely. I await your servicing.
Tell me of this place.
Enlighten me.
I should hope so - last time you and Lord Gortash were here I charged you both a pretty penny to help steal it.
I will grant a discount - a final discount, mind you. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
Thank you very much.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] *REUSE* [Player & Helsik] Produce and Take inventory construction anims.

Text.Value: There must be a catch?
Growl.
My wizard has spoken of little else, of late.

EditorData.logicalname: Gale is the DU's companion and talked of crown

Text.Value: Material wealth is a vain illusion. If you seek meaning and purpose, try compassion - give us a hint.
Of course, such a task will require quite the substantial donation to Lord Mammon's coffers. ([LOW_DevilsFee_ExpensiveHoH_b64a3173-46d0-e663-eaf6-ee900355256d])
Waive the fee and I'll add one of Raphael's artefacts to your collection.
I just killed a devil in his own home. You really don't want to test my patience.
Hand over [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6_ebf7de6b-4598-4feb-9c50-8083fc0fc59d] gold.
Raphael told me the Crown of Karsus was stolen from Mephistopheles - were you involved with that?
Leave.
So keen to return to the Hells. I supposed it's warm this time of year.
What a fascinating proposition. Ludicrous, of course, but fascinating nevertheless.
I found some interesting reading material downstairs. You're a diabolist, it seems.
I've already paid you plenty.
What business did we have in the Hells?
What business did Gortash have in the Hells?
Gortash stole the Crown of Karsus. Pissed off Mephistopheles, but rather intrigued another devil by the name Raphael.
Second. You will perform the rites yourself - I want absolute deniability. Here's the grimoire and necessary components.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] *REUSE* [Player & Helsik] Produce and Take inventory construction anims.
EditorData.NodeContext: helsik returns to a more serious mode of address here

Text.Value: Raphael's death is already causing quite a stir across the hells - it's a rare thing for a mortal to slay a devil of his stature.
His House of Hope is furnished with a great deal of treasures, many related to Karsus. But alas, he lacks the crown itself.
My time is money, and you've wasted too much of it. Get out of my sight.
Hmmm... The King of Avarice accepts your humble offering.
Ah, so you and Raphael have chatted recently? How... unusual.
Interesting. How exactly are you and our esteemed Archduke acquainted?
I welcome thee to the Devil's Fee - That's the spiel I give the more mundane customers.
My, what deep pockets you have.
Can you get me into the House of Hope?
It's your acquaintance with him I'm interested in - I found his name in your ledger.

EditorData.logicalname: player found ledger in devil's fee

Text.Value: I don't have that much money.
Perhaps it's time we paid Raphael a visit.
I've forgotten every single thing I've ever done before a few tendays ago.
It's customary for any salesperson to offer a free sample.
Leave.
*The Crown of Karsus? If the diabolist is to be believed, this would be no ordinary netherese relic. It could command the power of the gods themselves. Or the hells, if Raphael gets hold of it.*
My offer is - let me be a regular customer. I'd like to trade.
I presume you have returned to re-engage my services?
You rascals stole the Crown of Karsus. Pissed off Mephistopheles to no end. I expect you'll pay the price for that one day.
I'll be scattered across the Hells like a broken snuffbox. The price stays. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
I think it's about time we imposed ourselves on Raphael's hospitality for a change.
My apologies, your eminentness, but the Devil's Fee is closed for business.
You'll halve that price or I'll halve you.
Who died and made you the expert on Mammon's expectant pockets? I certainly didn't. The price stays. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
I don't have enough money.
No.
Yes, you are quite correct. The Crown of Karsus left the Vault, and an opportunity opened for a devil named Raphael.
I break people into the Hells. That's my thing.
I can feel the heat from that portal all the way down here. Keep it open as long as you need, but be sure nothing follows you through.
No.
Welcome back, devil-slayer. What can I do for you?
Why... The risk almost seems worth it when there's such pretty coins involved.

EditorData.NodeContext: they get distracted, enamoured by the gold, almost wistful

Text.Value: You... don't recall? Odd. I refer to the Crown of Karsus you and Lord Enver Gortash stole from Avernus with my help. The devil Raphael desires it.
Let me tell you what happens if Raphael even suspects I'm poking around his home.
Need anything before you head back to the hells?
Correction dear. Lord Mammon is ripping you off. It's sort of his thing.
Allow me to outline how this is going to work.
My memory is quite beyond hope, don't bother.
Your coin is always welcome here, and so are you, devil-slayer.
You stand before Mammon's Picklock. Latchkeeper of the Nine Hells. My business is not information, nor hellish curios, not really.
Well, I'm loathe to fully repeat myself... so I'll give you the whole tale. For a price, of course. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_3_01f129ea-b4dc-44b6-8154-9a948f876a82])
Fine. I'd like to be able to carry all of my precious stock without the need of a team of oxen.
I mean... I suppose that'll do. Stingy bastard.
*Along with the grimoire and components, Helsik hands you a note containing precise instructions for performing the ritual.*
Very well, here you go. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_2_463b0f43-5410-412d-aba3-875cf81c38ca])
Fine - take them.
Leave.
Very well, here you go. ([GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_6057ad05-9492-4630-9f0a-be548b134c54])
Then perhaps we should drop by and surprise Raphael? It'd make a nice change.
How may I be of further assistance?
We're old colleagues.
Then we have reached the end of our negotiations.
Your esteemedness returns! O joyous hour.
That doesn't make you dangerous, it makes you a liability. Get out of here before you test my patience.
You know, any saleswoman worth her salt offers a free sample.
Take this key, too. It unlocks the ritual room upstairs. There's a blood circle already drawn. Don't ask whose blood.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] *REUSE* [Player & Helsik] Produce and Take inventory construction anims.

Text.Value: Oh yes, I should think that'll do deliciously.
Now now. That would be but a drop in Mammon's oceanic coffers - you can do better.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] *REUSE* [Player & Helsik] Toss and catch object construction.

Text.Value: No chance.
Then I shall brush out Boo's fur - for we are going a-visiting.

EditorData.NodeContext: You've been told that the secret to this whole conspiracy lies in a devil's residence - you're not even questioning tha that's where you're going next.

Text.Value: Well well - it's been a while since I've had such discerning custom. Here, you may browse my more... curated selection.
Ahah. Ahah. Ahah. Quite the fitting token. Let it not be said that Lord Mammon's servant does not deal with paupers.

EditorData.AnimationTags: [Chris] *REUSE* [Player & Helsik] Toss and catch object construction.

Text.Value: Then to Raphael's house we must go.
The two of you wanted to steal something from Mephistopheles, so I punched a portal into the Archdevil's dusty vaults.
Lord Gortash wanted to steal something from Mephistopheles, so I punched a portal into the Archdevil's dusty vaults.
I'm done with this.
A handsome fee. The Gauntlets are yours to keep.
First, you were never here. We never spoke.
I'm leaving, this is ridiculous.
They're all yours.
That invalidates our deal, I'm afraid. I fulfilled my part of the bargain, so you owe me the fee I proposed initially.
Well, that was interesting, but I'd just like to see your wares.
I know you're a diabolist who worked for Gortash. What did you do for him?
Pay [GEN_CheckMagicPocketGold_5_8860ed48-ba5f-4b7b-82bf-f1220f967d41] gold.
Curios don't interest me. I'm interested in the hells themselves - a place called the House of Hope in particular.

Synopsis:
Default dialogue with Helsik. They are a trader and warlock in lower city. They grant us the ingredients to perform the ritual to the House of Hope. 



HELPFUL DEBUG COMMANDS:

oe LOW_GetItemsFromGortash - learn about Helsik from Gortash's note

oe LOW_KnowAllHelsik - learn that Helsik is a diabolist and that they know the way to the HoH

oe LOW_PortalHouseOfHope - set up the interactable HoH portal without having to do the ritual
